narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I developed a depth of thought and analysis that I didn't come close to having previously - allowing me to look at historical anachronisms with more clarity, and to draw comparisons between the present and past in ways that are more conducive to my own understanding of the world.
I learned how to engage in small seminar discussions with the professor and other students. It helped my public speaking and ability to quickly process information and respond to it.
I learned a lot about how to write analytical papers.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I'd say the only weakness of the course is that you have to opt in or out, it is very easy to check out, but if you are checked in even for a little bit, the class will draw you in in ways you would not have expected possible. The readings are engaging and actually help with your understanding of the material, but most of all they allow you to approach every discussion with more background knowledge and insight - and the discussions are so engaging that they encourage you to do the reading.
Good class overall, professor was very engaged in the material.
The course allowed for enriching, intellectual, free discussion.  The reading load was a lot and the discussions did not cover what we read often times.
This class is super interactive, which is amazing. There is a lot of reading, but as long as you keep on top of each reading and take care to understand it, its well worth it!

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would 100% recommend this course to another student, whether they have had previous engagement with the subject before or not.
Yes, especially if they are interested in Roman history.
Yes, Professor Stephens is great and facilitates really interesting discussion.

Yes! Dr Stephens is amazing, and all the classes are very interactive and student centred. No matter what your major is, this is a really fun class to take if you want an opportunity to share ideas and learn about a wide range of ancient historical events.
